|**********|
| UPCOMING |
|**********|

-Simplified scattering ray
  -origin of ray is negative light source dir multiplied by the light angle effect uniform
  -calculate light that has been scattered away already based of ray's length (ray's length: p1 to p2)
  -using left over light get new scattered light (current visible light)
